2026 Regular Session ACT No. 269 ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 477
BY SENATOR PRICE
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 11:164(A)(3) and R.S. 27:14(B)(2) and to enact R.S. 11:411(16),
3 relative to part-time public officials; to provide for the Louisiana State Employees'
4 Retirement System; to provide membership eligibility; to provide for the chairman
5 of the Louisiana Gaming Control Board; to provide for full-time employment; to
6 provide for compensation and benefits; to provide for an effective date; and to
7 provide for related matters.
8 Notice of intention to introduce this Act has been published.
9 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
10 Section 1. R.S. 11:164(A)(3) is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S. 11:411(16)
11 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
12 §164. Part-time public officials
13 A. Except as provided in Subsection B of this Section, the following elected
14 or appointed officials are hereby deemed to be part-time public servants who, based
15 on such part-time service, shall not participate in, or receive credit for service in, any
16 public retirement system, fund, or plan sponsored by the state of Louisiana or any
17 instrumentality or political subdivision thereof:
18 * * *
19 (3) Any member of a board or commission established by the state of
20 Louisiana or any instrumentality or political subdivision thereof unless authorized
21 by law enacted by two-thirds of the elected members of each house.
22 * * *
23 §411. Eligibility for membership
24 The membership of this system shall be as follows:
25 * * *
26 (16) The chairman of the Louisiana Gaming Control Board, appointed
27 and employed in such position on or after July 1, 2024.
