1 Section 2. R.S. 27:14(B)(2) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
2 §14. Compensation
3 * * *
4 B.(1) * * *
5 (2) The chairman of the board shall devote full time to his duties as chairman
6 and shall not engage in any other business or profession. During such service, the
7 chairman shall not earn compensation of any kind other than his salary paid as a
8 board member. The chairman shall be considered a full-time employee of the state.
9 Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, the chairman shall
10 be eligible for membership in the Louisiana State Employees' Retirement
11 System and shall not earn compensation of any kind other than that of an
12 adjunct professor and receive an annual salary equal in amount to that of a judge
13 of the courts of appeal of this state, as provided in R.S. 13:311 which amount shall
14 include expenses, benefits, emoluments, and any supplemental pay to which
15 such judges are entitled.
16 * * *
17 Section 3. This Act shall become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not
18 signed by the governor, upon expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature
19 by the governor, as provided by Article III, Section 18 of the Constitution of Louisiana. If
20 vetoed by the governor and subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become
21 effective on the day following such approval.
